                <div class="swiper-slide">
                    <p><strong>How To Use</strong></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Fill the device: Open the device and pour in one ampoule of serum.</li>
                        <li>Prepare the device: Twist on the needle head and leave upside down for 1–2 minutes.</li>
                        <li>Begin infusion: Stamp evenly across the face with 2–3 passes, then pat in any remaining serum.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <small class="c-note c-note--info">
                        <strong>Tip:</strong> Apply remaining serum after your treatment and allow it to absorb overnight.
                    </small>
                </div>
                <div class="swiper-slide">
                    <p><strong>Safety Guidelines</strong></p>
                    <p>Micro-Infusion is a simple treatment you can do at-home. No appointments and no downtime. It’s designed to be safe and easy to use, as long as your skin is clean and healthy.</p>
                    <p>Avoid using Micro-Infusion on active breakouts or broken skin, as it may spread bacteria. Always use a fresh, sterile needle head for each treatment, and apply SPF after use to protect your skin.</p>
                    <p>If you’re pregnant or have a medical condition, check with your doctor first.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="c-swiper-nav">
                <button class="c-swiper-button-prev"></button>
                <div class="c-swiper-pagination"></div>
                <button class="c-swiper-button-next"></button>
